field.name: CFT_CanonicalVersion
field.description: Version number of the SIAC's canonical message form. Must be first tag in header. Format: AAA.NN.NN i.e Format.MajorRelease.MinorRelease. e.g. FIX.01.00, XML.01.00 Note: Parallels FIX tags 8.

field.name: CFT_BodyLength
field.description: Message length in bytes to the Checksum field. Second tag in header. Note: Parallels FIX tag 9. 8/14/03: AEY: Max Canonical Message Size: 99999 bytes.

field.name: CFT_SIACMsgType
field.description: The CFT_SIACMsgType tag represents very general business transactions. This tag which must be third, would further categorize the transaction as it applies to SIAC systems. See table for Canonical Massage Type mapping. Note: Parallels FIX tag 35. 8/14/03: AEY: SIAC Message Types begin with the prefix "CFM_", are ALL CAPS, with a recommended maximum of 12 chars, including the prefix. SIAC Message Types may be used in conjunction with subtypes, i.e. see CFT_MsgSubtype tag. 2/13/04: Max length is increased to 25 chars.

field.name: CFT_MsgSubtype
field.description: SIAC Message Subtypes allow for further subdivision within a SIAC Message Type. 8/14/03: AEY: SIAC Message Subtypes begin with a prefix "CFS_", preferably with a max length of 12 chars, including the prefix. 02/13/04: Max length increased to 25 chars.

field.name: CFT_MsgOrigin
field.description: Identifies where message came from. This is a free format string. If the QMGW is the source of the message, this tag will contain the "emitter id". For applications, this tag may hold the origin system name, queue name, process name.

field.name: CFT_MsgDest
field.description: Identifies where a message is destined for. This is a free format string. This can hold a destination system name, process name, queue name.

field.name: CFT_MsgSeqNo
field.description: The internal message sequence number assigned for tracking between systems. Note: Parallels FIX tags 34,5024 8/14/03: AEY: With the development of the SIAC Message ID tag (CFT_SMID), the CFT_MsgSeqNo tag has not been really used because applications get the message sequence number from the CFT_SMID tag. However, since this tag is a required tag, set it to 0.

field.name: CFT_Flags
field.description: 2/25/02: CFT_Flags is a bit-field (bits 0 thru 15) used to indicate certain states. The values of the bit-fields can be queried via the getfield() CS API. bit 0: CFT_PossdupInd bit 1: CFT_GapfillInd bit 2-15: fillers

field.name: CFT_MsgSendTime
field.description: Timestamp when system sent message. Note: Parallels FIX tag 52.

field.name: CFT_MsgPriority
field.description: Provide override of FIFO message handling to support transactional time constraints.

field.name: CFT_MsgSeverity
field.description: Categorize message criticality (E.g. INFO, WARN, ...)

field.name: CFT_SourceMsgFmt
field.description: An indicator of the format of the original message (FCS, FIX,..) 8/18/03:AEY The format of this tag has been enhanced to be a colon delimited string of formats to allow for representation of n-layers should a canonical msg pass thru more than one message layer (e.g. CFT_SourceMsgFmt=JMS:FIX:...:) If there is only 1 format, then the tag will simply contain the format name.

field.name: CFT_SessionID
field.description: Info about the session where the message originated. This field would allow retention of context info required to respond to sender.

field.name: CFT_HostMsgID
field.description: This field allows host specific message ID (Eg: TA Number, Firm Branch Seq, etc.) 10/23/2002 Deprecated in favor of CFT_SMID to represent SIAC Message ID, and tags such as CFT_Firmsymbol, CFT_BrCode, CFT_BrSeq, etc.

field.name: CFT_AuthorizeHandle
field.description: Entitlements of the sender.

field.name: CFT_LogMsgPtr
field.description: Pointer to where copy of the message received, is stored.

field.name: CFT_DeliveryTimeout
field.description: Abort deliver after time indicated by this field.

field.name: CFT_HdrRawDataLen
field.description: Generic Tag defined for the length of any Raw Data field that users can use to add in the header portion of the message. It is strongly recommended for users to use this tag for Rawdata, instead of creating a new tag. If this generic tag is always used for raw data tag, this will solve backward compatibility issues, where the receiver of a message does NOT have to recompile with a new Raw Data Tag, because any release of CF APIs will detect this tag. Note: 12/18/2002: this tag was renamed from CFT_CanonicalHdrRawDataLen to CFT_HdrRawDataLen.

field.name: CFT_HdrRawData
field.description: Generic Tag defined for any Raw Data field that users can use to add in the header portion of the message. It is strongly recommended for users to use this tag for Rawdata, instead of creating a new tag. If this generic tag is always used for raw data tag, this will solve backward compatibility issues, where the receiver of a message does NOT have to recompile with a new Raw Data Tag, because any release of CF APIs will detect this tag. Note: 12/18/2002: this tag was renamed from CFT_CanonicalHdrRawData to CFT_HdrRawData

field.name: CFT_MsgOrigSystem
field.description: Defines the system from which the message was sent. Format is hierarchical, logical application system name is required (example:SDOT), lower level subsystem names are optional.

field.name: CFT_MsgDestSystem
field.description: This field defines the system to which the message was sent if using point to point protocol. It is not applicable in pub/sub protocol. The format is hierarchical, logical application system name is required (example:SDOT), lower level subsystem names are optional.

field.name: CFT_ReplyToAddr
field.description: The address for the receiving application to respond to, if a response is required and the return address is not the MsgOrig. This is used between sending and receiving applications, where the message originating application is not responsible for receiving the responses. The format of the value is determined by the protocol used.

field.name: CFT_SMID
field.description: This is the SIAC Message ID. The CFT_SMID is a unique identifer of a message in the enterprise. The format of the SMID is: emitter:instance:subject:sequence The 4 components of the SMID are colon separated. The components are: emitter ID: fixed 6 byte string, identifier of the publisher of the message instance number : fixed 2-byte int subject: 1-40 characters sequence number: up to 9 digits

field.name: CFT_EventID
field.description: CFT_EventID is an identifier for message events. This is a required tag for Operator Alert Message Type. (see Common Software Logging API)

field.name: CFT_RefID
field.description: Generic reference ID. It can be used as a context field that will be returned by the receiver of the message, as is (no change to the value of the field). For example, the Gap Fill requester uses it to pass a Gap Fill ID to the Gap Fill process, which turns around this tag so that when the message is received, it can be referenced.

field.name: CFT_UQ_SafestoreAddress
field.description: TANDEM QM Safestore file byte address of message

field.name: CFT_UQ_FilesetID
field.description: TANDEM QM Safestore fileset ID

field.name: CFT_UQ_MsgSource
field.description: Entity name of message originator in TANDEM CS Network

field.name: CFT_UQ_MsgSubSource
field.description: Message originator sub-qualifier in TANDEM CS Network.

field.name: CFT_UQ_MsgDestination
field.description: Destination entity name for which the message is destined in TANDEM CS

field.name: CFT_UQ_MsgSubDest
field.description: Destination entity name sub-qualifier in TANDEM CS Network.

field.name: CFT_UQ_CMSource
field.description: Type + source from CM Header

field.name: CFT_UQ_CMDest
field.description: Type + destination from CM Header.

field.name: CFT_UQ_Flags
field.description: Bit field for the UQPROC informational flags (e.g.: POS-DUP indicator). Refer to Tags 90016 thru 90031 for bit .

field.name: CFT_JMS_MsgOrigin
field.description: This tag is the JMS Message Origin tag. This is the canonical equivalent of the JMSMsgOrigin tag in the JMS Header. This tag holds the JMS Client ID when CFT_SIACMsgType=JMS, CFT_MsgSubtype=CFS_CAN. Used by Common Software JMS Gateway. What does it hold for other JMS Types? format?

field.name: CFT_JMS_MsgDest
field.description: This tag is the canonical equivalent of the JMSDestination field in the JMS Header. Currently used by the CS JMS Gateway.

field.name: CFT_JMS_DeliveryMode
field.description: This is the Canonical equivalent of the JMS Header field, JMSDeliveryMode. It is the delivery mode specified when the JMS message was sent. Used by the Common Software JMS Gateway.

field.name: CFT_JMS_MsgID
field.description: This is the canonical equivalent of the JMS Header field, JMSMessageID, which contains a value that uniquely identifies a JMS message. Used by the Common Software JMS Gateway.

field.name: CFT_JMS_Timestamp
field.description: This is the canonical equivalent of the JMS Header field, JMSTimestamp. It contains the time a message was handed off to a provider to be sent. Used by the Common Software JMS Gateway

field.name: CFT_JMS_CorrelationID
field.description: This is the canonical equivalent of the JMS Header field, JMSCorrelationID, which a JMS client can use to link one message with another. Used by the Common Software JMS Gateway

field.name: CFT_JMS_ReplyToAddr
field.description: This is the canonical equivalent of the JMS Header field, JMSReplyTo. Contains the Destination supplied by a JMS client when a message is sent. It is the destination where a reply to the JMS message should be sent. Used by Common Software JMS Gateway.

field.name: CFT_JMS_Redelivered
field.description: This tag is the Canonical equivalent of the JMSRedelivered field in the JMS Header. If a JMS client receives a message with the JMSRedelivered field set, it is likely, but not guaranteed, that the message was delivered but not acknowledged in the past.

field.name: CFT_JMS_Expiration
field.description: This is the canonical equivalent of the JMS Header field, JMSExpiration. When a message is snet, its expiration time is calculated as the sum of the time-to-live value specified on the send method and the current GMT value.

field.name: CFT_JMS_Type
field.description: This is the Canonical equivalent of the JMS Header field, JMSType. Contains a JMS Message Identifier supplied by a client when a message is sent

field.name: CFT_JMS_Priority
field.description: This is the canonical equivalent of the JMS Header field, JMSPriority, which contains a JMS' message priority. Used by the Common Software JMS Gateway

field.name: CFT_ReasonCode
field.description: Reason code to further qualify reqeust or response message. For example, GFP uses the reason code to indicate the reson for a NACK response.

field.name: CFT_BodyRawDataLen
field.description: Generic Tag defined for the length of any Raw Data field that users can use to add in the body portion of the message. It is strongly recommended for users to use this tag for Rawdata, instead of creating a new tag. If this generic tag is always used for raw data tag, this will solve backward compatibility issues, where the receiver of a message does NOT have to recompile with a new Raw Data Tag, because any release of CF APIs will detect this tag. Note: 12/18/2002: this tag was renamed from CFT_CanonicalBodyRawDataLen to CFT_BodyRawDataLen

field.name: CFT_BodyRawData
field.description: Generic Tag defined for any Raw Data field that users can use to add in the body portion of the message. It is strongly recommended for users to use this tag for Rawdata, instead of creating a new tag. If this generic tag is always used for raw data tag, this will solve backward compatibility issues, where the receiver of a message does NOT have to recompile with a new Raw Data Tag, because any release of CF APIs will detect this tag. 12/18/02: This tag was renamed from CFT_CanonicalBodyRawData to CFT_BodyRawData. 2/28/03: For CFM_EMAIL Messages, this tag will hold the body of the email, whether it is text or binary data.

field.name: CFT_EncapsulationLen
field.description: Length of contained message in bytes Supports encapsulation of message received from previous system. Note: Parallels FIX tag 95. Note: 12/18/2002: Changed from a header tag to a body tag.

field.name: CFT_EncapsulationMsg
field.description: Actual encapsulated message. Note: Parallels FIX tag 96. Note: 12/18/2002: Changed from a header tag to a body tag.

field.name: CFT_PublisherListLen
field.description: The Gapfill Process (GFP) keeps track of what publishers it is servicing. CFT_PublisherListLen is the length of the value of the CFT_PublisherList tag. This tag is used in the CFM_SMIDSTAT response message from the Gapfill process.

field.name: CFT_PublisherList
field.description: The Gapfill Process (GFP) keeps track of what publishers it is servicing via a list of emitter ids. CFT_PublisherList holds a list of emitter ids, separated by a vertical bar "|". This tag is used in the CFM_SMIDSTAT response message. See also CFT_PublisherListLen.

field.name: CFT_AdditionalSeqNum
field.description: This field is used by the publisher or the GapFillProcess to pass additional sequence number field when appropriate. For example, the publisher uses this field to pass previous sequence number when a sequence number is reset by operator command. The GapFillProcess uses this field to pass the next available sequence number in the case of hard NACK.

field.name: CFT_AdditionalInstanceNum
field.description: This field is used by the publisher or the GapFillProcess to pass additional sequence instance number field when appropriate. For example, the publisher uses this field to pass previous instance number when a instance number is reset by operator command. The GapFillProcess uses this field to pass the instance number for the next available message for the subject specified in the NACK response.

field.name: CFT_NYSEReceiveTime
field.description: Contains a system-produced timestamp of the time an order or order modification (or drop-copies of such) is received by a NYSE system from a NYSE order-management system or a proprietary/third party order-management system. Note: NYSE order-management systems and proprietary/third-party order management systems are not required to provide FloorAvailableTime for orders and order modifications since that time will always be later than the NYSE_Receive_Time

field.name: CFT_UnitOfTradeCode
field.description: Contains the unit of trade code for the security specified in this order. Unit of Trade values from the STK file are 100, 50, 10, 1 Mapping: [SuperDOT - SECURITY_BODY/STK_UOT]

field.name: CFT_PriceDenominationCode
field.description: Contains the binary value of the price denominator code (field is 8 bits). See the PRICE_DENOMINATION_REF entity for values. Mapping: price_dp [SuperDOT - MSR_BODY/PRICE_DENOM_CODE/]

field.name: CFT_ClearingFirmSymbol
field.description: Contains the Clearing Firm's Symbol (1 to 4 alphas). 10/25/2002: Deprecated in favor of ClearingFirmAlphaID

field.name: CFT_ClearingNumber
field.description: Contains the Specialist Clearing Number (1 to 9999). Mapping: [SuperDOT - SECURITY_BODY/SPCLR] 10/25/2002: Deprecated in favor of ClearingFirmID (for member firm clearing firm id) or SpecClearingFirmID (for specialist clearing firm id)

field.name: CFT_ExchangeCode
field.description: Contains information regarding the market used to identify the security. Identifies the Stock Exchange: 1=NYSE 2=AMEX. 01/30/2002: AEY "N" = NYSE (default) "I" = NYSE (IIEDS)

field.name: CFT_SubmittingProcessID
field.description: The ID of the process submitting the DMS request

field.name: CFT_DMSconnectionID
field.description: ID of the FESC DMS connection

field.name: CFT_DMSmsn
field.description: The message sequence number of the DMS request - assigned by the requesting application

field.name: CFT_DMSstatusCode
field.description: Status (response) code of the processed DMS request.

field.name: CFT_FirmSymbol
field.description: Member Firm mnemonic - not necessarily the same as CompSendID 4 bytes max - entering firm

field.name: CFT_OrderModCode
field.description: The code value for the type of order modification. 01 = Rule 123 order acceptance 02 = Cancelled order 04 = Cancelled/Replaced order 05 = Rule 123 cancel acceptance 06 = Rule 123 cancel/replace acceptance

field.name: CFT_OrderOriginCode
field.description: Designates the System origination or source of the order. Valid values are: 1-SuperDOT 2-DropCopy 3-BBSS. 12/19/03: AEY: This tag is used by FESC-HIST

field.name: CFT_ChildOrderCode
field.description: 7/25/2003: This tag indicates whether a child order is a Partial or a CAP order. Note: Currently, there is a CFT_CAPInd tag to indicate whether or not something is a CAP order or not. Phase I of PTTP uses the CFT_CAPInd tag. With the advent of partials, which is another type of child order, we are introducing CFT_ChildOrderCode to allow applications to distinguish b/w CAPs and partials, which would consequently allow us to deprecate the CFT_CAPInd tag.

field.name: CFT_FloorViewTime
field.description: Contains the time the floor broker actually views or accepts an order or order modification.

field.name: CFT_FloorAvailableTime
field.description: Contains a system-produced timestamp of the time that details of an order or order modification are first displayed or entered into a device on the NYSE trading floor.

field.name: CFT_OrderKey
field.description: Primary key for the database orders table

field.name: CFT_OrderModKey
field.description: Primary key into the database order_mod table

field.name: CFT_OlrlprlCode
field.description: Defines whether an order is a Odd Lot, Round Lot, or Partial Round Lot.

field.name: CFT_OddLotQuantity
field.description: Defines the Odd Lot Quantity

field.name: CFT_DerivedRepSeqNum
field.description: FIX tag 17 (ExecID) is a string variable, assigned by a firm, that identifies an execution message. The Drop Copy application converts tag 17 to an integer (using a CRC-like algorithm) in order to populate the Report_Sequence_Number attribute in the Drop Copy database.

field.name: CFT_Handlnst
field.description: Same as Tags 21 and 9407. This canonical tag is required so as to make the distinctions between FIX 4.1 and FIX 4.2 transparent to the FESC DMS.

field.name: CFT_MinQty
field.description: Same as Tags 9408 and 110. This canonical tag is required so as to make the distinctions between FIX 4.1 and FIX 4.2 transparent to the FESC DMS.

field.name: CFT_MaxFloor
field.description: Same as tags 9409 and 111. This canonical tag is required so as to make the distinctions between FIX 4.1 and FIX 4.2 transparent to the FESC DMS.

field.name: CFT_MaxShow
field.description: Same as tags 9410 and 210. This canonical tag is required so as to make the distinctions between FIX 4.1 and FIX 4.2 transparent to the FESC DMS.

field.name: CFT_ContraBroker
field.description: Same as tags 9421 and 375. This canonical tag is required so as to make the distinctions between FIX 4.1 and FIX 4.2 transparent to the FESC DMS - Mnemonic of the contra-party to the trade. 10/11/2002: This tag was deprecated in favor of CFT_BadgeID. 05/11/2004: Tag deprecated in favor of CFT_ContraFirmID

field.name: CFT_NoContraBrokers
field.description: Same as tags 9423 and 382. This canonical tag is required so as to make the distinctions between FIX 4.1 and FIX 4.2 transparent to the FESC DMS. - The number of contra broker records (number of contra parties) associated with this report - set by FESC - The number of contra broker records (number of contra parties) associated with this report - set by FESC

field.name: CFT_ContraTradeQuantity
field.description: Same as tags 9434 and 437. This canonical tag is required so as to make the distinctions between FIX 4.1 and FIX 4.2 transparent to the FESC DMS. 10/11/2002: Deprecated in favor of CFT_ContraTradeQtyShares.

field.name: CFT_RoundLotQuantity
field.description: defines the Order Round Lot

field.name: CFT_MsgProductId
field.description: Product Code/Identified, Uniguely defined for each PDP product. All messages defined heerein will contain the value 101

field.name: CFT_MsgProductVersion
field.description: Version Id - Used to identify message formats/revisions for a given product. the initial version is always set to the value '1'; subsequent revisions will increase this value monotonically. All messages defined herein will contain a version ID of '1'.

field.name: CFT_MsgRetransFlag
field.description: A flag that indicates whether this is an orignal, retransmitted, or 'replayed' message. Valid values include; '1' - Orignal message '2' - Retransmitted message '3' - Message replay '4' - Retransmission of a 'replayed message'

field.name: CFT_MsgTimeStamp
field.description: Timestamp associated with message publication, the value is defined as the number of seconds that have elapsed since 12:00:00 January 1, 1970 (i.e. 'UNIX' time format).

field.name: CFT_MsgBodySize
field.description: The size in bytes of the immediatetly succeeding (contiguous) message body

field.name: CFT_MsgBlockId
field.description: Publication time of message block in UNIX time format

field.name: CFT_MsgPubTime
field.description: The time represents the time slot to which this data belongs. It defined to an 6 characters ASCII string in military time format (HHMMSS); note that 1:05PM is 130500.

field.name: CFT_MsgNumRecord
field.description: The number of data messages in this transmission. this value should include the End Block Message.

field.name: CFT_MsgPosDup
field.description: This flag is set to binary '0' for normal transmissions. It should contain the value binary '1' if the block contains any message that have already been transmitted.

field.name: CFT_MsgMetaData
field.description: Contained the Canonical structure definition.

field.name: CFT_MsgType
field.description: Message Identifier within product type. Message type values from 1-99 are reserved for control messages. 10 - Begin Acknowledge 50 - Metadata request message 51 - Metadata response message 60 - Begin block message 61 - End block message 62 - No data message 110 - Intra-day message 111 - Intra-day index message 112 - 30 day message 113 - 30 day index message

field.name: CFT_MsgReq
field.description: Metadata is message specific; this field indicate the message type for which metadata is being provided. The tag is used in conjuction with tag 20254.

field.name: CFT_NoShares
field.description: Number of shares (express in round lots) for a given container.

field.name: CFT_NotHeldInd
field.description: 1/7/2002 "Not Held" Indicator see Template B This tag, together with the CFT_AllNone and CFT_CAPInd, fulfills the function of the All or None CAP Ind field in Template B.

field.name: CFT_CAPInd
field.description: 1/7/2002 This is the CAP (Conversion and Parity) Indicator flag. Valid Values: "Y" = it's a CAP order "N" or tag not sent = it's not a CAP order This tag, together with CFT_AllNone and CFT_NotHeld fulfills the functionality of the ALL or None CAP Ind field in Template B.

field.name: CFT_ManualType
field.description: 1/30/2002 CFT_ManualType is a tag associated with Manual Trades. 10/11/2002: Tag Deprecated because Manual Trades & Busts of Manual Trades can be distinguished by using CFT_MsgSubType.

field.name: CFT_TickComment
field.description: 01/30/2002 WHen a report is entered from the floor, then a tick filing comment is entered. Note that it's max size (=10 bytes) was based on the sizes of MemoA + Memo B.

field.name: CFT_XCHInd
field.description: 1/30/2002 CFT_XCHInd is an indicator for ex-clearing house. Identifies a trade that will be settled outside the normal clearing processing. Note: all other values used by XCH in the TPE (Template E) are not in use EXCEPT for PRIN. However, PRIN is now specified thru the CFT_PrinOffsetID.

field.name: CFT_SettlementInst
field.description: Settlement Instruction Codes

field.name: CFT_RequestID
field.description: Heartbeat Identifier tag This is set in a Heartbeat request message type and returned in a Heartbeat response message.

field.name: CFT_Text
field.description: Optional tag for a Heartbeat Message Type. If this tag is present in a heartbeat request, then it must be returned in a heartbeat response message. 8/21/2002: AEY Optional tag for Reject Message Type. Contains text for reject reason.

field.name: CFT_MsgRcvTime
field.description: Time stamp of last message recieved 2/28/03: For the TWMHS interface: This is the time stamp of a previously received email referenced by the CFT_EmailThreadID.

field.name: CFT_KeyRepeat
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the number of keys for a table

field.name: CFT_KeyName
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the name of a key for a table

field.name: CFT_KeySize
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the size in bytes of a key for a table

field.name: CFT_KeyPrimary
field.description: Used in GRMS to send whether a key for a table is primary(True) or not(False)

field.name: CFT_KeyUnique
field.description: Used in GRMS to send whether the key of a table is unique(True) or not(False)

field.name: CFT_KeyModifiable
field.description: Used in GRMS to send whether the key for a table is modifiable(True) or not(False)

field.name: CFT_KeyFieldRepeat
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the number of fields in a key for a table

field.name: CFT_KeyFieldId
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the numeric identifier associated with the field of a key

field.name: CFT_KeyFieldSize
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the size in bytes of a field in a key

field.name: CFT_KeyFieldType
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the data type of a field in a key

field.name: CFT_KeyFieldValue
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the value of a field in a key

field.name: CFT_KeyFieldLabel
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the label associated with a field in a key

field.name: CFT_TableRepeat
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the number of tables in a system

field.name: CFT_TableName
field.description: Used in GRMS to send the name of a table in a system

field.name: CFT_FIXMsgSeqNum
field.description: Corresponds to the FIX tag MsgSeqNum[34]. As per FIX spec, defined as: integer message sequence number. Tag is used by FESC R123 Drop Copy Application.

field.name: CFT_ContraBadge
field.description: Holds the badge of the clearing firm of the contra party to a trade. This is a repeating field in an execution report.

field.name: CFT_GroupTANumber
field.description: 1/31/2002 Group TA Number. If order is an OARS or MOC order (orders submitted before or after market hours), then this field contains the Group TA number. Note: Please also see CFT_GroupTACode (if you need the variable length group TA code).

field.name: CFT_HbAction
field.description: a "command" type of a tag that indicates whether or not to start/stop heartbeats

field.name: CFT_HbTime
field.description: If present, interpreted as either start time (HbAction=Start) or stop time (HbAction = Stop). If absent, effect of command is immediate

field.name: CFT_HbQty
field.description: If present, the number of HB messages to generate. Absence of this field means heartbeats will be generated continuously. Applies when HbAction = Start.

field.name: CFT_HbInterval
field.description: If present, it's the interval b/w heartbeat msgs in seconds. If absent, the default interval is used. Applies when HbAction = Start.

field.name: CFT_TransactionEntryTime
field.description: This tag corresponds to the time that a transaction hits the first SIAC system. A transaction is defined by the Canonical MsgTYpe:Subtype combination. For example, if a CFM_ORDER:CFS_REG message hits CMS at 10:00, then CFT_TransactionEntryTime is 10:00. This is not the same as CFT_MsgSendTime. CFT_MsgSendTime changes as the message hops along different systems. The CFT_TransactionEntryTime reflects the time the msg hits the first SIAC system and is thus the same as the msg traverses from system to system.

field.name: CFT_RefSMID
field.description: 2/06/2002 CFT_RefSMID refers to the 4-tuple SMID of a gap'd message. This is of SMIDType (i.e. emitter:instance:subject:seqno). This tag is a required tag for a gapfill request/response message.

field.name: CFT_RefSMIDCount
field.description: 2/6/2002 CFT_RefSMIDCount tag is used in conjunction with the CFT_RefSMID tag for gapfill request/response messages. The CFT_RefSMID will contain the starting sequence number for a range of gap'd messages, while CFT_RefSMIDCount will indicate how many messages are missing.

field.name: CFT_ProcName
field.description: CFT_ProcName refers to the process name that generates the Operator ALert Message. This is a required tag for the Operator Alert Message Type (see CS Logging API)

field.name: CFT_ProcID
field.description: CFT_ProcID: process id or PID

field.name: CFT_BrokerBadgeID
field.description: This is the initiating broker badge ID, used for CAP2.

field.name: CFT_ParentOrderMFirm
field.description: CAP2 parent order member firm 4-char mnemonic , if order is entered thru BBSS.

field.name: CFT_ParentOrderBrCode
field.description: CAP2 Parent Order Member Firm Branch Code (for orders entered thru BBSS)

field.name: CFT_ParentOrderBrSeq
field.description: CAP2 Parent ORder Branch Sequence - for CAP orders entered thru BBSS.

field.name: CFT_ParentOrderTANumber
field.description: CAP2 Parent Order TA Number - for CAP orders entered thru BBSS 6 bytes(fixed). note: format "A 0026" has been eliminated and replaced with " A0026". 8/21/2002: Please see CFT_ParentOrderTACode if you need the variable length TA.

field.name: CFT_ParentOrdXRefID
field.description: This is the canonical equivalent of FIX Tag 9450 - ParentOrdXRefId. Format: 4 char alpha for member firm of the parent order - if member firm mnemonic is less than 4 character, left justify blank- fill, followed by 1 space, then up to 22 characters using ASCII character Set from Octal 40 (Hex 20) to Octal 176 (Hex 7E) for the parent order id. Used only for CAP2 orders entered via propietary OMS.

field.name: CFT_SecondaryOrderID
field.description: same as FIX tag SecondaryOrderID[198]. As per FIX spec, defined as: assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the OrderID used by an exchange or executing system.

field.name: CFT_InstitutionSymbol
field.description: The mnemonic of a sponsored institution (Entering Entity)

field.name: CFT_OrderSizeLimit
field.description: Maximum share size allowed for an order submitted by an institution (shares)

field.name: CFT_CreditLimit
field.description: Maximum dollar limit allowed for all unsettled orders submitted by an institution

field.name: CFT_AlertLevel1
field.description: Percent of CreditLimit at which to issue a first credit alert

field.name: CFT_AlertLevel2
field.description: Percent of CreditLimit at which to issue a second level alert

field.name: CFT_EEViewAllow
field.description: Specifies whether an institution can view it credit alerts

field.name: CFT_LastOrderRejected
field.description: Code to indicate if the last order received by ADOT was rejected

field.name: CFT_ChangeTransType
field.description: Code to indicate the source of an ADOT table change message

field.name: CFT_FESCChangeID
field.description: Unique identifier of the ADOT table change entry

field.name: CFT_UpdateUserID
field.description: ID of the browser user that submitted the ADOT table change

field.name: CFT_SubmitResponseCode
field.description: Code returned by SuperDOT to ADFESC upon SDOT's processing of an ADOT table change request

field.name: CFT_ADOTActionType
field.description: Action type code to be specified in an ADOT action message

field.name: CFT_ADOTActionSubType
field.description: Action subtype code specified in an ADOT action message

field.name: CFT_CreditUsed
field.description: Dollar value of today's orders plus the dollar value of prior day's unsettled trades

field.name: CFT_AccountState
field.description: Code to indicate the state of the EE account as a result of the most recent order processed by ADOT

field.name: CFT_LastSDOTTimestamp
field.description: Timestamp of the last ADOT message that updated CreditUsed 12/19/03: AEY: This tag is still in use for ADOT processing

field.name: CFT_SDOTBranch
field.description: Branch code of the submitted order 10/22/2002: Deprecated in favor of CFT_BrCode

field.name: CFT_SDOTSeqNumber
field.description: Branch sequence number of the submitted order 10/22/2002: Deprecated in favor of CFT_BrSeq

field.name: CFT_SDOTSecuritySymbol
field.description: Security symbol in SDOT format 10/24/2002: Deprecated in favor of CFT_StockSymbolSDOT

field.name: CFT_SDOTOrderInst

field.name: CFT_SDOTOrderType
field.description: SDOT order type code 10/11/2002: Deprecated in favor of CFT_OrderTypes

field.name: CFT_SDOTOrderTimestamp
field.description: Time of day the order was received by SDOT (for order rejects) 10/11/2002: Deprecated in favor of CFT_SDOTEntryTime

field.name: CFT_ValueToday
field.description: Dollar value of today's executed orders

field.name: CFT_FirmLastUpdate
field.description: Time of the most recent member firm change to credit parameters

field.name: CFT_EntryBooth
field.description: The entering booth's mnemonic. 01/30/2002: AEY up to 3 char string, ID of the Booth where the report originated. CMS still has 2 char Booth IDs; but SDOT has been modified to handle 3 char.

field.name: CFT_DestBooth
field.description: The destination booth's mnemonic.

field.name: CFT_RecoveryInfo
field.description: A safestore file's disk address.

field.name: CFT_CreditIncrement
field.description: An adjustment to the "credit used" on an Anonymous DOT account.

field.name: CFT_SDOTOrderQuantity
field.description: SuperDOT's order quantity. 10/22/2002: This tag deprecated in favor of CFT_OrderQuantityShares.

field.name: CFT_RecoveryThread
field.description: This is used in SuperDOT. It specifies what XRQF the current message came from. Valid values are from 1-5.

field.name: CFT_FullUpdateSeqNum
field.description: The value begins at '1' at the start of a session and increases monotonically with each Full Update Message published (this includes Full Update Messages generated in response to a Full Update Request Message).

field.name: CFT_DeltaUpdateSeqNum
field.description: Represents the sequence number of the Delta Update message (this value is set to zero [0] in Full Update Messages). This value increases monotonically with every Delta Update Message published for each stock symbol.

field.name: CFT_PacketNum
field.description: Represents the sequence number of this packet (for multi-packet messages).

field.name: CFT_PacketTotal
field.description: Indicates the total number of packets in this message (for multi-packet messages). This tag is used in conjunction with the PacketNum tag.

field.name: CFT_TradingHalt
field.description: This tag is set to 'T' (for 'trading') by default; Display Book will set this flag to 'H' when trading for stock has been halted.

field.name: CFT_MPV
field.description: Minimumm Price Variation. Refers to the minimum permissible price movement of a stock symbol. With the inception of decimals, the MPV has generally been a penny.

field.name: CFT_Denominator
field.description: Represents the price denominator.

field.name: CFT_LastSalePrice
field.description: The price at which a given stock last traded before the Market close.

field.name: CFT_NumBuyPoints
field.description: The Number of Buy Points represented in this message. This number is used to determine how many buy point triplets follow this field.

field.name: CFT_NumSellPoints
field.description: The Number of Sell Points represented in this message. This number is used to determine how many sell point triplets follow this field.

field.name: CFT_DetailBuyPrice
field.description: Each DBK price comprises three elements: - a numerator, - a denominator, and - the symbol s MPV (minimum price variation). Both the denominator and the MPV are constants; thus, they will appear only once in each published data message. The numerator will appear once for each price point. This tag is used in conjuction with the DetailBuyCount and DetailBuyQuantity tags.

field.name: CFT_DetailBuyCount
field.description: The number of orders open at a given price. This tag is used in conjunction with the DetailBuyPrice and DetailBuyQuantity tags.

field.name: CFT_DetailBuyQuantity
field.description: Represents the quantity (in terms of Unit of Trade) that exists for a given buy price. This tag is used in conjuction with the DetailBuyPrice and DetailBuyCount tags.

field.name: CFT_DetailSellPrice
field.description: Each DBK price comprises three elements: - a numerator, - a denominator, and - the symbol s MPV (minimum price variation). Both the denominator and the MPV are constants; thus, they will appear only once in each published data message. The numerator will appear once for each price point. This tag is used in conjuction with the DetailSellCount and DetailSellQuantity tags.

field.name: CFT_DetailSellCount
field.description: Represents the number of orders open at a given sell price. This tag is used in conjunction with the DetailSellPrice and DetailSellQuantity tags.

field.name: CFT_DetailSellQuantity
field.description: Represents the quantity (in terms of Unit of Trade) that exists for a given sell price. This tag is used in conjuction with the DetailSellPrice and DetailSellCount tags.

field.name: CFT_ClearingFirmID
field.description: 01/03/2002 4 bytes fixed string e.g. "0161" equivalent of Template H, Clearing Firm Clearing Number

field.name: CFT_SourceOfOrderCode
field.description: 01/07/2002 Valid Values: "CMS" = Firm (CMS) "SAX" = SAX "DBK" = Display Book "BBSS" = BBSS "TW" = TW (added 6/04) "HHLD" = HHLD (added 6/04) (see Template H)

field.name: CFT_PrinCommentCode
field.description: 01/03/2002 same as Template H (Principal Activity Comment) 1-2 byte canned comment for AWOs. This field comes from DBK and is forwarded to SAH.

field.name: CFT_PrinOffsetID
field.description: 01/03/2002 same as Principal Indicator in Template H

field.name: CFT_ServiceQualityInd
field.description: 01/03/2002 Valid Values for Reports: "P" = penetrated "T" = touched " " or tag not sent = not penetrated, not touched, not bypassed (this tag, in conjunction with CFT_ServiceQualityTime, represents the Service Quality Data field in Template H)

field.name: CFT_ServiceQualityTime
field.description: 01/03/2002 This tag, in conjunction with CFT_ServiceQualityInd, represents Service Quality Data field in Template H.

field.name: CFT_SourceOfReportCode
field.description: 01/07/2002 Valid Values: "CARD" = card post "SAX" = sax "DBK" = display book "BBSS" = card booth "SDOT" = sdot "HHLD" = handhelds "TW" = TW (added after 6/04)

field.name: CFT_PriceOverrideInd
field.description: this tag is used to override the price at which to execute an order (which could be a worse price than the order price)

field.name: CFT_OddLotAdjType
field.description: 01/03/2001 Required for Odd Lot Adjustment Reports Valid Values: "A" = add "C" = cancel Note: The values for "Type" in Template H has now been divided into 4 different canonical tags, AWOType, ReportType, ERCActivityType, OddLotAdjType

field.name: CFT_AWOType
field.description: 01/03/2002 Used in AWO Reports Valid Values: "1" =PRIN to Crowd Report "2" = PRINT to ITS Report "3" ITS Name Chg Admin "4" = PRIN to OARS/MOC/Block To show bust of an AWO: use CFT_MsgSubtype=CFS_AWOERC and CFT_ERCActivityType=4.

field.name: CFT_OrderInstruction
field.description: 1/7/2002 Order Instruction Code for an order. In the case of a cancel replace, this tag will hold the order instruction for the replacement order.

field.name: CFT_TIFCodes
field.description: 1/7/2002 TIF (Time in force) Code mnemonics used in conjunction with CFT_OrderTypes. In the case of a cancel replace, this is the time-in-force code of the replacement order. Valid values: OPG = execute order on open GTC = good till cancelled for LMT-II OC = immediate or cancel FOK = fill or kill DAY = day (for lmt II) GTX = GTX(GTC, eligible for crossing session I) XPR = xpr (xpress order) GTD = Good till Date (added as of 1/26/04) To represent a day market order: CFT_OrderTypes="MKT" && CFT_TIFCodes=DAY To represent a day limit order: CFT_OrderTypes=LMT && CFT_TIFCodes=DAY To represent a good till cancel, market order: CFT_OrderTypes=MKT && CFT_TIFCodes=GTC To represent a good till cancel, limit order CFT_OrderTypes=LMT && CFT_TIFCodes=GTC

field.name: CFT_OrderTypes
field.description: 1/7/2002 Type of Order received. In the case of a cancel replace, this would be the order type for the replacement order.

field.name: CFT_TotalExecQtyShares
field.description: This is the total # of shares executed forthe order so far. This is across all reports. Note: NOT the same as sum of all contra qty for an execution

field.name: CFT_GFPPubInfoList
field.description: The Gapfill Process (GFP) keeps track of the publishers it is servicing. The CFT_GFPPubInfoList an array of publisher info records. Each record is currently 8 bytes in length; it is made up of the "subject name" and the "maximum sequence # published by the GAPFILL process" for that subject name. This tag is used in the CFM_SMIDSTAT response message sent by the Gapfill process to the application that sent the CFM_SMIDSTAT request message.

field.name: CFT_GFPPubInfoLen
field.description: The Gapfill Process (GFP) keeps track of which publishers it is servicing. CFT_GFPPubInfoLen indicates buffer size of publisher info records held in CFT_GFPPubInfoList. This tag is used in the CFM_SMIDSTAT response message sent by the GFP to the process that sent the CFM_SMIDSTAT request message.

field.name: CFT_TotalDeletedQtyShares
field.description: Total # of shares deleted from the order and taken out of SDOT.

field.name: CFT_GFPPubInfoSize
field.description: The Gapfill Process (GFP) keeps track of the publishers it is servicing. CFT_GFPPubInfoSize tag indicates the size of each record in the CFT_GFPPubInfoList array. Currently, CFT_GFPPubInfoSize is 8 bytes; but this may change in the future.

field.name: CFT_TWArrivalTime
field.description: Time when a message hit TradeWorks (TW).

field.name: CFT_ReportBoothID
field.description: Id of the booth where the report originated 6/7/2004: AEY For TW, this will hold the TW logical address.

field.name: CFT_Array
field.description: 2/20/02: (PTTP) CFT_Array is an array of fixed length SMIDs. Used in the CFM_EOD, CFS_MaxSeqResponse message. Note: the length of CFT_Array cannot exceed the maximum block size (=32K).

field.name: CFT_ArraySize
field.description: Indicates the size of the array (in bytes)

field.name: CFT_Count
field.description: CFT_Count indicates the number of SMID items in CFT_Array.

field.name: CFT_ElementSize
field.description: CFT_ElementSize indicates the size of each element in an array. For PTTP, CFT_ElementSize refers to the size of each SMID in CFT_Array.

field.name: CFT_TotalCount
field.description: For PTTP, CFT_TotalCount indicates the total number of SMIDs sent across all CFM_EOD, CFS_MaxSeqResp messages.

field.name: CFT_TotalMsgCount
field.description: Sum Total of Max Sequence Numbers sent across all emitters during the day, i.e. total message sent across all emitters for the day. For example: Last Msg Count for GM: 101 Last Msg Count for IBM: 99 Last Msg Count for T: 10 Then, CFT_TotalMsgCount=210 Note: For PTTP, this tag is used for EOD Processing, as a required tag in the CFS_MAXSEQTOTAL message sub-type. This tag is will be sent b/w the QMGW and the EODP process and will be forwarded by EODP process to SWOPI as well.

field.name: CFT_CxlLeavesShares
field.description: 8/21/2002: The Leaves Quantity on a Cxl w/ LVS message (in shares). Cannot be an odd lot.

field.name: CFT_LeavesTIFCodes
field.description: The LvsTIFCode indicate the time-in-force for the leaves quantity on a cancel w/ leaves message. There is no LvsTIFCode on a cancel replace.

field.name: CFT_PossDupFlag
field.description: This is the generic possdup tag, used to indicate if a particular message (at the application level) is a poss-dup or not.

field.name: CFT_RefOrderInstruction
field.description: This tag is used to reference an original order's instruction code in a Cancel Replace or Cancel Balance Replace Message Type.

field.name: CFT_RefOrderTypes
field.description: This tag is used to reference the order type of an original order in a Cancle Replace Message. This tag maps to "TYPE" in Template D.

field.name: CFT_RefTIFCodes
field.description: This tag references the original order's time-in-force (TIF) codes in a Cancel Replace Message. This tag is used in conjuction with CFT_RefOrderTypes.

field.name: CFT_RefOrderQuantityShares
field.description: This tag references the original order's quantity in shares and is used in a cancel replace message. This tag represents the quantity to be cancelled.

field.name: CFT_RefStopPx
field.description: On a cancel replace, this tag references the Stop Price associated with the original order (if order is a Stop or Stop Limit order)

field.name: CFT_RefLimitPx
field.description: On a cancel replace, this tag references the original order's limit price.

field.name: CFT_RefSettlementInst
field.description: On a cancel replace, Settlement Instruction Code for the original order.

field.name: CFT_RefAllNoneInd
field.description: A round lot market or limit price order that must be executed in its entirety or not at all. Unlike Fill or Kill orders, AON orders are not treated as cancelled if they are not executed as soon as represented in the trading crowd.

field.name: CFT_RefCAPInd
field.description: On a cancel replace, this tag indicates whether the original order was a CAP order or not.

field.name: CFT_RefNotHeldInd
field.description: On a cancel replace, this tag indicates if the original order was "held" or "not held". If "not held" is set to "Y", then the firm executing the order is not held to the best execution requirements, and may be able to make some discretionary decisions.

field.name: CFT_RefTryStop
field.description: On a CXL Replace, this tag indicates whether an original order had the try-to-stop indicator set. Try To Stop: Used in specialist driven markets to direct the specialist to try and stop the order

field.name: CFT_RefDniDnr
field.description: On a CXL Replace, this tag references whether an original order's dni/dnr attribute. This tag maps to the "DNI/DNR" field in Template D. Do Not Increase: A limit order to buy, a stop order to sell, or a stop-limit order to sell which is not to be increased in shares on the ex-dividend date as a result of a stock dividend or distribution. Do Not Reduce: A limit order to buy, a stop order to sell, or a stop-limit order to sell that is not to be reduced in price by the amount of an ordinary cash dividend on the ex-dividend date. A do-not-reduce order applies only to ordinary cash dividends; it should be reduced for other distributions - such as when a stock goes ex stock dividend or ex rights.

field.name: CFT_RefAccountType
field.description: IN a CXL REPLACE message, this tag references the original order's account type. For a more detailed description of account types, pls see Appendix F of CMS Manual

field.name: CFT_Line3F4TextLen
field.description: This is the length of the CFT_Line3F4Text tag value.

field.name: CFT_ReplOrderTACode
field.description: This is paired order pointer that holds the TA Code of the replacement order. (pls see CFT_ReplOrderTANumber also)

field.name: CFT_RefOrderTACode
field.description: This tag is the paired order pointer that references the original order TA code information. (pls see CFT_RefOrderTANumber also)

field.name: CFT_TestReqID
field.description: same as FIX tag TestReqID[112]. As per FIX spec, defined as: Identifier included in the Test request message to be returned in resulting heartbeat

field.name: CFT_ClientId
field.description: Used to identify clients connected to a server

field.name: CFT_Version
field.description: Used to send version strings of an application. 2/26/03: In GRMS, we send it as 0220 if our release number is 02.20.05. In EVS, we send it as 282201always, as the original release of IGS that came with EVS had the release number 28.22.01 2/28/03: This tag is required for CFM_EMAIL messages between TM and MHS. Format has not been finalized yet.

field.name: CFT_Symbol
field.description: Used to send Security Symbols. 3/16/2004: Tag is used by IGS and EVS. Format is: 6 char symbol root, blank filled 10 char symbol suffix, blank filled

field.name: CFT_ExchId
field.description: Used to send a Security Exchange Id. 10/24/2002: Deprecated in favor of CFT_ExchangeCode.

field.name: CFT_NewsType
field.description: Used to send identifiers for News messages.

field.name: CFT_RBA
field.description: USed to specify an RBA(Relative Byte Address) of a file.

field.name: CFT_StateCondition
field.description: Used to describe the state of a state machine.

field.name: CFT_StatusNo
field.description: Used to send a status number.

field.name: CFT_TimeInterval
field.description: Used to specify a time interval. 8/28/03: AEY time interval is specified in seconds.

field.name: CFT_MsgTotal
field.description: Used to send the total number of messages.

field.name: CFT_MsgPeriod
field.description: Used to send periods between messages.

field.name: CFT_Indicator
field.description: Used to send any kind of boolean indications.

field.name: CFT_IndexValue
field.description: Used to send Index values.

field.name: CFT_MsgDate
field.description: Used to send Dow Jones News message date.

field.name: CFT_MsgTime
field.description: Used to send Dow Jones News message time.

field.name: CFT_DisplayDate
field.description: Used to send Dow Jones News display date.

field.name: CFT_DisplayTime
field.description: Used to send Dow Jones News message display time.

field.name: CFT_SymbolList
field.description: Used to send a list of space separated Security Symbols.

field.name: CFT_SymbolCount
field.description: Used to send number of Security Symbols in a SymbolList.

field.name: CFT_ReqType
field.description: Used to send a Request Type.

field.name: CFT_PortNo
field.description: Used to send a TCP/IP Port number.

field.name: CFT_InputDevStat
field.description: Indicates the current status of the input device.

field.name: CFT_InputMsgCount
field.description: Used to count the total number of messages.

field.name: CFT_LineCounter
field.description: For EVS: Used to determine the number of lines used for the stats command. The fields that follow this field will be used as repeat fields (LineState, PrimaryBackUpInd, ReceiveData and ActiveLine.)

field.name: CFT_LineState
field.description: for EVS: The indicates the state of the current line. The line state can only be "UP" or "DOWN". Valid Values: "D" = down "U" = up

field.name: CFT_PrimaryBackupInd
field.description: For EVS: This indicator is used to determine which line is primary or backup. Valid Values: "P" = primary "B" = backup

field.name: CFT_ReceiveData
field.description: For EVS: Used to determine if the current line is receiving Dow Jones Index data. Valid Values: "Y" = yes "N" = no

field.name: CFT_ActiveLine
field.description: For EVS: This field is used to determine if the current line is active. The active line is the line that is processing data messages from the Dow Jones index feed. Valid Values: "Y" = yes "N" = no

field.name: CFT_VendorSeqNum
field.description: For EVS: This is the sequence number of the input vendor feed, which is passed to the Core SIAC host systems.

field.name: CFT_OrderTACode
field.description: CFT_OrderTACode is the turnaround code associated with an order. It is a variable length string of 3-6 characters, which is the preferred TA format. (Compressed version)

field.name: CFT_GroupTACode
field.description: This tag is the Group TA Code used for OARS or MOC orders. The format for this TA Code is a variable 3-6 character string. (see also CFT_GroupTANumber - format: fixed 6 char)

field.name: CFT_CxlOrdRefTACode
field.description: For a cancel/replace, the TA number of the order that this order cancelled (the link to the original order). For the cancelled order, this is the TA number of the replacement order. The format for this TA number is variable 3-6 character string.

field.name: CFT_ParentOrderTACode
field.description: CAP2 Parent Order TA Code - for CAP orders entered thru BBSS. Format is variable CAP2 Parent Order TA Code - for CAP orders entered thru BBSS. Format is variable 3-6 character string.

field.name: CFT_BBSSInterfaceID
field.description: Maps to the Intersystem Template header, byte 8 of internal data. It Contains the BBSS interface ID for orders coming in from BBSS. Please note: Byte 8 and 11 of the intersystem template internal data header is overloaded (see also CFT_CMSDeviceNumber)

field.name: CFT_CxlQuantityShares
field.description: For a simple cancel or cancel w/ lvs messages: Quantity to be cancelled in shares.

field.name: CFT_ExecDate
field.description: This tag will hold the trade date. It is a required tag for all types of executions. (see CFT_ExecTime for the execution time)

field.name: CFT_CMSDeviceNumber
field.description: Maps to bytes 8 and 11 of internal data in the Intersystem Template header. For orders coming in from MFs, byte 8 can hold either a rotary device number or a multi-line firm indicator. If MF comes in via multi-line, then byte 11 holds the multi-line terminal id.

field.name: CFT_OCSArrivalTime
field.description: Time the message arrived at OCS

field.name: CFT_ERCTransactionTime
field.description: Time when the ERC (Execution Report Correction) was done. Required tag for ERC Reports.

field.name: CFT_CMSCAPFlag
field.description: The CMSCAPFlag indicates which the device type a member firm is connected to (examples of device types thru the CAP system are bisync, CAP TCP/IP FIX TCP/IP). This flag is commonly known as ICAP (from CMS Perspective) and UCAP (from SDOT Perspective). Note that the CMS values are actually translated to SDOT values. This indicator is useful for SDOT which has occasionally different processing code for FIX and FCS (e.g. CXL Repl handling)

field.name: CFT_ClearingFirmAlphaID
field.description: Member Firm Clearing Firm Mnemonic

field.name: CFT_CMSNodeID
field.description: CMS Node ID Identifier This tag is a byte in the "Internal Data" field in the message header of the intersystem template.

field.name: CFT_FirmName
field.description: This tag holds the full name of a member firm. (e.g. Goldman Sachs)

field.name: CFT_RefOrderTANumber
field.description: This is the TA Number of the original order (referenced on a Cxl Replace message) also see CFT_RefOrderTACode (variable 3-6 chars)

field.name: CFT_SideBuySellInd
field.description: Used in CFM_OCS_SIDES message. Indicates whether the side is a for a buy or a sell side.

field.name: CFT_BookedInd
field.description: CFT_BookedInd: boolean flag to indicate if an order was booked (to DBK) from BBSS.

field.name: CFT_OddLotInvSign
field.description: This tag indicates whether the specialist is long or short on his current odd lot inventory.

field.name: CFT_OddLotInvValue
field.description: This value indicates the # of shares by which a specialist's odd lot inventory is long or short.

field.name: CFT_OddLotInvAlertValue
field.description: Line code can be anything that makes sense for the specialist. It is always a whole number. Generally, it is very low because a specialist would not want to tie up all of his shares to handle oddlot trades. He would much rather hold the shares in his round lot inventory so that they can be traded. If he wants to keep 4 UOTs of stock in his odd lot inventory bucket, then his LINE CODE would be 4 and the amount of shares in his bucket goes from -399 to + 399. If he made the linecode 10, then he would be tying up almost a 1000 shares (-999 to +999). That is why for the most part, everyone uses 1. Only up to 100 shares would be tied up (-99 to +99) and the position minding function takes care of replenishing the inventory and emptying the inventory when necessary.Note: Line Code is not the same as UOT.

field.name: CFT_CMSArrivalTime
field.description: Time a message arrives at CMS. This is the preferred tag to CFT_CMSEntryTime

field.name: CFT_HHLDArrivalTime
field.description: Message arrival time at the Floor HandHeld Device

field.name: CFT_SDOTArrivalTime
field.description: Time a message got to SDOT

field.name: CFT_SourceOfActivityCode
field.description: On an ERC: This tag is used to indicate the source of a correction (ERC) on an execution. On a Cancel: This tag is used to indicate the source system of a cancel message. On a Admin: This tag is used to indicate the source system of an admin message.

field.name: CFT_PriorityInsertInd
field.description: This tag is set to "Y" when an order is entered on the floor or from SAX at a different time other than the current time.

field.name: CFT_PriorityInsertTime
field.description: Time when a priority insert order was inserted.

field.name: CFT_DJ_StockInd
field.description: Dow Jones Stock Indicator

field.name: CFT_ConvBond
field.description: Convertible bond field is used for the ancillary screen

field.name: CFT_OddLotPricingCode
field.description: Determines the Pricing Code for the auto-executed odd lot. The pricing codes are: next sale last sale quote next or last sale

field.name: CFT_PSSArrivalTime
field.description: Message arrival time at PSS.

field.name: CFT_OrderLocationCode
field.description: Identifies in which system the order resides currently

field.name: CFT_AggrLastTime

field.name: CFT_MoreGapfillAvail
field.description: 8/13/2003: This bit tag is bit 4 in the CFT_Flags bit_flag in the Canonical header. When an application requests for gapfills, it provides the starting SMID of the gap'd msg plus a SMID count to indicate how many msgs from the starting SMID need to be filled. The CS Gapfill server will only send a maximum of 'max chunk size' number of gapfill msgs at a time. The 'max chunk size' is a configurable parameter in the sdf file. 'max chunk size' may not necessarily equal the # of SMID count requested by the application in the gapfill request. This enhancement was done to prevent any one application from using up all the bandwidth. Note: A 'max chunk size' of 0 would indicate that the Gapfill server should just send all requested gapfill msgs, no chunking. The CFT_MoreGapfillAvail tag is used as follows: If an application requests for gapfills that is greater than the max chunk size, the following actions will happen: a) Gapfill Server responds with 'max chunk size' gapfills. The last gapfill message in the stream will have the CFT_MoreGapfillAvail bit tag set to indicate that more gapfill msgs are available for the application. b) When the application detects that the CFT_MoreGapfillAvail bit tag is on, it will need to send another Gapfill request message, starting from the last gapfill SMID sequence # received +1 to retrieve the next stream of gapfill msgs. c) If all gapfill msgs have been retrieved, the CFT_MoreGapfillAvail bit tag is set to 0. If an application requests for gapfill msgs less than 'max chunk size', then the CFT_MoreGapfillAvail bit tag is set to 0.
